1. a method that returns the sum of two integers

Given two variables, each assigned a seperate integer.
  
Add the first integer with the second.
Return the sum and assign to the variable sum.

Print the value of sum.

Formally ###

START 

SET first_integer
SET second_integer
SET sum = first_integer + second_integer

PRINT sum

END


2. a method that takes an array of strings, and returns a string that is all those strings concatenated together

Given an array of strings.
Assign an empty string called all_strings

Iterate through the array of strings.
  Add each string of the array to the empty string all_strings
  Iterate for the entire length of the array.

Print all_strings

Formally ###

START

SET string_array # array of all 
SET all_strings # empty string
SET iterator = 1

WHILE iterator < length of string_array
  SET all_strings = all_string + current value of string_array
   iterator = iterator + 1

PRINT all_strings

END

3. a method that takes an array of integers, and returns a new array with every other element

Given an array of integers.
Set an iterator at 0.

Iterate through the array of integers.
  IF the iterator is even (divisible by 2)
    save integer in new_array
  Incrememnt the iterator by 1
  End when iterator is equal to the length of the integer array.

Print new_array





